<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-07-10T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-07-10T18:00:00-05:00" n="89" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d89">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">211.62/82: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Germany</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Sackett</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-07-10T19:00:00-04:00">July 10, 1930—7
                                p.m.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>68. Your No. 79, July 8, 4 p.m. President’s full power signed July 9
                            authorizing you to sign extradition treaty shown German Embassy,
                            Washington, which will advise German Government by cable of its
                            satisfactory character. Proceed to signature. Full power will be mailed
                            first opportunity for delivery by you to Foreign Office.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
